Job DescriptionYou have:

- Built and led successful data scientist teams focused on identification of health risks, including biomarkers, behavioral risks, environmental risks, and/or social determinants of health associated with human diseases, particularly age-related chronic diseases, in business, academic, and/or government organization(s);

- Experience in legacy and contemporary human disease risk modeling tools and methods including ML/DL/AI, and co-authored peer-reviewed scientific manuscripts describing your use of these tools to advance our understanding of human health;

- Demonstrated ability to solve difficult health and data science challenges;

- Broad experience using large publically available data sets in support of, or conduct of, human clinical research;

- Been recognized by peers as a leader in health-focused and data science.

You are:

- A systems thinker, most comfortable working from first principles;

- A constant user of the scientific method to approach problems;

- Excited about building something new, big, and important from the ground up;

- Exceptionally focused on (and care a great deal about) integrity, trust, respect, and hard work;

- Innovative but realistic, and focused on delivering results;

- Prepared to wait for the second marsh mellow before eating the first one;

- Excited by this description.

You will:

- Architect, build, implement, and constantly improve our company’s human health-focused data science efforts;

- Work closely with human-centered designers, health scientists, technologists, and diverse health ecosystem partners and clients;

- Help build and be a critical part of a diverse high-performing leadership team and company;

- Represent our company on health-focused data science with partners, clients, Board of Directors, and investors;

- Amaze your colleagues, peers, and our competitors.



